HEADWORD: Decachordon
<hw>Dec`a*chor"don</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>deka`chordos</grk>
tenstringed; <grk>de`ka</grk> ten + <grk>chordh`</grk> a string.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>An ancient Greek musical instrument of ten strings,
resembling the harp.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Something consisting of ten parts.</def> <rj><au>W.
Watson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Decacuminated</ent>⟦br⟧
